{
  "texts": [
    "ConclusionThis study heavily relies on newspaper articles; however, the topic of ChatGPT or GenAI becomes less controversial after more than three-quarters of the discussion.",
    "Therefore, some recent but related events may not have been reported in newspapers.",
    "Given that universities' attitudes towards these new technologies have become more aligned after half a year of development in Hong Kong, this article is valuable as it has scaffolded how universities evolved through the three phases (procrastination-remediation-adaptation) during the most intense period.",
    "The identification of these three phases allows universities to position themselves and push themselves to move along these phases in the future as the emergence of ChatGPT/ GenAI is only one of the technological advancements that can shake the education field.",
    "Other technological advancements will continue to impact the higher education setting and require a change in policy and management.During the literature review for this study, the authors were not surprised to find that studies regarding how universities in limited-access regions respond to the use of ChatGPT are rare."
  ]
}